Rules:
- Output JSON EXACTLY in this structure:
{
  "subsections": [
    { "subsection_id": "(5)a", "subsection_text": "..." },
    { "subsection_id": "(5)b", "subsection_text": "..." }
  ]
}

CRITICAL TEXT PRESERVATION RULES:
- Preserve ALL punctuation EXACTLY as it appears in the source text,
  including periods (.), commas (,), semicolons (;), colons (:), brackets,
  quotation marks, and line breaks.
- Do NOT rewrite, rephrase, summarize, normalize, or reflow sentences.
- Do NOT merge sentences.
- Do NOT split sentences unless explicitly instructed below.
- The presence of periods (.) alone MUST NOT cause any split.

How to split (ONLY when explicitly allowed):
- Split into subsections ONLY IF:
  1) Logical list items are separated by semicolons (;) AND
     each item is a complete independent obligation; OR
  2) Checkbox items [x] appear.
- When splitting:
  - Preserve the exact wording, punctuation, spacing, and order.
  - Assign subsection_ids strictly in order of physical appearance:
    (5)a, (5)b, (5)c â€¦
  - For checkbox items, create:
    (5)[x]1, (5)[x]2, (5)[x]3 in order of appearance.

STRICT PROHIBITIONS:
- Do NOT split on periods (.).
- Do NOT split on commas (,).
- Do NOT split paragraphs into multiple subsections.
- Do NOT invent or infer structure.
- Do NOT change formatting.
- Do NOT include markdown.

TEXT (verbatim source, position-bound):
{text}
